only bakinfi powder made mb mJ\nfrom eream of tartar\n=g- J l I 1 M *-41\nhall secured for\nANNIVERSARY BALL.\nThe joint committees of Albany and\nLaramie lodges, Odd Fellows, have se\ncured Maenenrchor hall for the anni\nversary ball to be given the night of\nApril 28 and Nlethe's orchestra to fur.\nnish the music.\nNOTED BALL PLAYER\nVISITED IN CITY.\nAmong the visitors to the city yes-\nCARPET ECONOMY\nIt will be of interest to prospective purchasers of Carpets\nto know that we have, by special arrangement with a large\ncarpet house, installed a Cut Carpet Department and are now\nprepared to show you how you can make a saving of from\n20 to 25 per cent on your Carpet purchases.\nThe reason of this is that instead of carrying a stock of\nCarpets we have a large number of patterns and grades in\none anil two-yard lengths from which you car make your\nselections. We then send in the order and have the Carpet\nmade. In this way we do not have a large amount tied up\nin Carpet stock, and can sell at decidedly lower figures than\nif we did.\nCome in and let us prove to you that we can save you\nmoney.\nLARAMIE DRY GOODS CO.\n\u201cTHE ECONOMY STORE.\u201d\nI\nCAR OF\n-=FLOUR=-\nIs here. It is the kind that makes the best bread.\nCall for\nSMITH HARVEY\nTh* Quisk sr\u00bbc\u00abr\u00bb.\n21 Ht\u00abnd Street T*l*#hon\u00ab 14 Red.\n[the BEST ROCK SPRINGS COAiJ\nI In town; also Sampo Coal, same price as Hanna coti), but a better qual- I\nI Ity; for sale by\nS. A. CRAWFORD', j\nI Office Grand Avenue, between Second and Third. \u2019Phone 57 Black.\nTHE FIRST NATIONAL BANK\nLARAMIE, WYOMING.\nCHPITHL HND SURPLUS $120,000\nTRANSACTS A GENERAL BANKING BUSINESS\nUNITED DEPOSITARY\nDIRECTORS:\nEDWARD IVIN3ON, Pr\u00ab\u00bb. A. C. JONES CaaHlar.\nOTTO GRAMM ORA HALEY, H. D. BEEMER.\nAlbany County National Bank Blook.\nterday were Fred Clark of Ogden, tbe\nnoted ball ipilayer, and Mrs. Clark, who\n1 were on their way east for a visit and\nwho stopped over here between trains\n-for a visit with Mr. and Mrs. Fred\nf Cameron and other friends. Mr. and\nMrs. Clark are warm personal friends\nof Mr. and Mrs. Bailey Cornwell at\nOgden and brought word from them\nto their of friends.\nDaily Republican, 50 cents a month","height":"23244","width":"16536"}}
